<subSubSection id="C3216524FFDFFFA2FF43FEDEFE0CFD97" pageId="6" pageNumber="186" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8B8436AFFFDFFFA2FF43FEDEFE0CFD97" blockId="6.[136,1452,335,614]" pageId="6" pageNumber="186">
<bibRefCitation id="EFAA4B5EFFDFFFA2FF43FEDEFE9BFE9B" author="Schumann, K." box="[136,336,335,362]" pageId="6" pageNumber="186" pagination="117 - 200" refId="ref8376" refString="Schumann, K. (1886) Tilliaceae. Flora Brasiliensis, enumeratio plantarum in Brasilia hactenus detectarum: quas suis aliorumque botanicorum studiis descriptas et methodo naturali digestas partim icone illustratas 12 (3): 117 - 200. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 454" type="journal article" year="1886">Schumann (1886)</bibRefCitation>
described 
<taxonomicName id="4C3B4D2CFFDFFFA2FE02FEC1FD06FE98" box="[457,717,335,362]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malvaceae" genus="Luehea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malvales" pageId="6" pageNumber="186" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="uniflora" variety="gracilis">
<emphasis id="B94FEABDFFDFFFA2FE02FEC1FD8BFE98" box="[457,576,335,361]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="186">L. uniflora</emphasis>
var. 
<emphasis id="B94FEABDFFDFFFA2FDBCFEDEFD06FE98" box="[631,717,335,361]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="186">gracilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
based on 
<emphasis id="B94FEABDFFDFFFA2FCF6FEDEFC08FE9B" box="[829,963,335,362]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="186">
<collectorName id="26CE5379FFDFFFA2FCF6FEDEFC4EFE98" box="[829,901,335,361]" pageId="6" pageNumber="186">Riedel</collectorName>
1397
</emphasis>
, and several duplicates are kept in different herbaria. 
<bibRefCitation id="EFAA4B5EFFDFFFA2FF3DFEE2FE5FFE7F" author="Cunha, M. C. S." box="[246,404,371,398]" pageId="6" pageNumber="186" pagination="83 - 84" refId="ref7362" refString="Cunha, M. C. S. (1980) Consideracoes sobre Luehea candicans Mart. (Tiliaceae), uma nova combinacao - Luehea candicans var. gracilis (Schum.) M. C. S. Cunha. Bradea, Boletim do Herbarium Bradeanum 3 (11): 83 - 84." type="journal article" year="1980">
<collectingCountry id="F32C763FFFDFFFA2FF3DFEE2FEF4FE7C" box="[246,319,371,397]" name="Saint Helena, Ascension and Tristan da Cunha" pageId="6" pageNumber="186">Cunha</collectingCountry>
(1980)
</bibRefCitation>
indicated this collection from 
<collectorName id="26CE5379FFDFFFA2FD35FEE2FC50FE7F" box="[766,923,371,398]" pageId="6" pageNumber="186">Herbarium M</collectorName>
as the ‘holotype’, but this specimen was not found (
<collectorName id="26CE5379FFDFFFA2FF10FE09FEF6FE43" box="[219,317,408,434]" pageId="6" pageNumber="186">H. Esser</collectorName>
, pers. comm.). 
<collectorName id="26CE5379FFDFFFA2FE25FE06FDE7FE40" box="[494,556,407,433]" pageId="6" pageNumber="186">Since</collectorName>
<bibRefCitation id="EFAA4B5EFFDFFFA2FDFFFE06FD35FE43" author="Schumann, K." box="[564,766,407,434]" pageId="6" pageNumber="186" pagination="117 - 200" refId="ref8376" refString="Schumann, K. (1886) Tilliaceae. Flora Brasiliensis, enumeratio plantarum in Brasilia hactenus detectarum: quas suis aliorumque botanicorum studiis descriptas et methodo naturali digestas partim icone illustratas 12 (3): 117 - 200. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 454" type="journal article" year="1886">Schumann (1886)</bibRefCitation>
did not specify any herbarium and since we have not found any specimen in 
<collectorName id="26CE5379FFDFFFA2FE99FE2AFE22FE27" box="[338,489,443,470]" pageId="6" pageNumber="186">Herbarium B</collectorName>
where he worked (
<bibRefCitation id="EFAA4B5EFFDFFFA2FD1AFE2AFC28FE24" author="Stafleu, F. A. &amp; Cowan, R. S." box="[721,995,443,470]" pageId="6" pageNumber="186" refId="ref8497" refString="Stafleu, F. A. &amp; Cowan, R. S. (1976 - 1988) Taxonomic Literature: A selective guide to botanical publications and collections with dates, commentaries and types, 2 nd ed., Smithsonian Libraries, last updated 28 Jun. 2012. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 48631" type="book" year="1976">Stafleu &amp; Cowan 1976</bibRefCitation>
–1988: 400), we designate 
<emphasis id="B94FEABDFFDFFFA2FAEAFE2AFA60FE27" box="[1313,1451,443,470]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="186">
<collectorName id="26CE5379FFDFFFA2FAEAFE2AFAA2FE24" box="[1313,1385,443,469]" pageId="6" pageNumber="186">Riedel</collectorName>
1397
</emphasis>
(P 
<date id="FF85106FFFDFFFA2FF54FE71FED8FE0B" box="[159,275,480,506]" pageId="6" pageNumber="186" value="2949-02-14">
<collectingDate id="EFC1E987FFDFFFA2FF54FE71FED8FE0B" box="[159,275,480,506]" pageId="6" pageNumber="186" value="2949-02-14">02142949</collectingDate>
</date>
) as the 
<typeStatus id="5480880DFFDFFFA2FEA7FE4EFE18FE08" box="[364,467,479,505]" pageId="6" pageNumber="186">lectotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName id="4C3B4D2CFFDFFFA2FE32FE71FCCAFE08" box="[505,769,479,506]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malvaceae" genus="Luehea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malvales" pageId="6" pageNumber="186" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="uniflora" variety="gracilis">
<emphasis id="B94FEABDFFDFFFA2FE32FE71FDB9FE08" box="[505,626,479,505]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="186">L. uniflora</emphasis>
var. 
<emphasis id="B94FEABDFFDFFFA2FD60FE4EFCCAFE08" box="[683,769,479,505]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="186">gracilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, according to Art. 9.3 of the ICN. It was chosen as the most representative, complete, and best-preserved specimen congruent with the protologue’s description. 
<bibRefCitation id="EFAA4B5EFFDFFFA2FB2EFD92FAB4FDEF" author="Cunha, M. C. S." box="[1253,1407,515,542]" pageId="6" pageNumber="186" pagination="83 - 84" refId="ref7362" refString="Cunha, M. C. S. (1980) Consideracoes sobre Luehea candicans Mart. (Tiliaceae), uma nova combinacao - Luehea candicans var. gracilis (Schum.) M. C. S. Cunha. Bradea, Boletim do Herbarium Bradeanum 3 (11): 83 - 84." type="journal article" year="1980">
<collectingCountry id="F32C763FFFDFFFA2FB2EFD92FAE5FDEC" box="[1253,1326,515,541]" name="Saint Helena, Ascension and Tristan da Cunha" pageId="6" pageNumber="186">Cunha</collectingCountry>
(1980)
</bibRefCitation>
has restored the nomenclatural priority, recombining 
